title: no more spots after applying makeup

title: its ok not great
review: i recently tried the elf hydrating face primer and i have to say my experience with it has been a bit mixed while it didnt quite meet my personal expectations i have noticed that my niece absolutely loves itone of the standout features of this primer is its lightweight formula it feels incredibly light on the skin almost as if youre wearing nothing at all it doesnt leave any greasy or heavy residue which is a big plus for those with oily or combination skini also appreciate the hydrating properties of this primer it does a decent job of moisturizing the skin leaving it feeling soft and supple i noticed that it helps to smooth out any dry patches providing a more even canvas for makeup applicationadditionally this primer claims to fill in pores and fine lines and while it does a decent job in that regard i didnt notice a significant difference in the appearance of my pores or fine lines it provided a subtle smoothing effect but not to the extent that i was hoping forone aspect that i found particularly beneficial was the natural matte finish it helped to control shine and kept my makeup looking fresh for a longer duration however i did find that it emphasized any texture on my skin such as acne scars or bumpswhile i had mixed feelings about this primer my niece who has different skin concerns absolutely loves it she has dry skin and found that this primer provided the perfect amount of hydration for her it also helped to prolong the wear of her makeup and created a smooth base for foundationin conclusion the elf hydrating face primer is a lightweight and hydrating option that provides a natural matte finish while it didnt completely meet my personal expectations in terms of porefilling and linesmoothing abilities it has proven to be a great fit for my nieces dry skin if you have similar skin concerns this primer may be worth a try

title: love the formula and great intro to cream contour
review: just looking for an affordable introduction to practice my cream contour nyx surprised me with it formula which is easy to apply easy to work with and lasts all day i compare it to other products ive tried such as colourpop and abh creams and maybelline and wet n wild liquidsi gave it four stars because i think i can safely assume you will only use  colors its great for finding a match for your medium shade but theres only going to be one darker shade and one maybe two light shade i wouldnt necessarily buy this again now that i know what colors i actually use and would then look for a larger pan kit from nyxalso of note i use the technique where you apply the contour before foundation i mention this because i apply the contour a little heavier and lean into the drama once you apply foundation you can blend out and soften it up i think this technique also helps with the ease of use and product longevity if you use a different technique i imagine you might have a different experience with this product but maybe not

title: gives a natural result
review: this eyebrow palette is very small you could pop this in your handbag for touch ups quite easily i bought the medium brown as i am quite fair skinned the left hand colour is the wax the right hand colour is the settingfilling powder one of the application brushes is firmer than the other and is for applying the wax the softer one is for the powder the brushes are very small though so i think i might buy some full size ones as the supplied ones are ok for carry around but are a bit fiddly to useapplication was easy enough and im a total beginner at this as a something lady i have quite sparse brows now so i was looking for something to add a little colour and definition to what little i have left the wax part of the procedure went on nicely and helped smooth and define the brow shape the powder needs a little more care as it can be pretty dark if you use too much if dark and thick is what you want im sure you could achieve that but us older gals need something more subtle and it does that too as i hope you can see from my beforeafter photo my first attemptoverall my first impression of this little kit is pretty good im actually quite new to doing makeup and ive been searching for something reliable for my eyebrows i tried a propelling wax pencil that broke off after a dozen uses and wouldnt have lasted long anyway there was so little in it and also a traditional brow pencil that proved impossible to sharpen reliably two expensive and disappointing products theres very little to go wrong with this type of palette and brush style of brow grooming and the price makes it a good value product i figure it should last me a few months at least so im hopeful this is the answer for me i can recommend you give it a try if you have experienced similar problems and frustrations with eyebrow products as i have

title: this thing works amazingon some people
review: yes its like clear pasty glue and thats why it worked for me im a pro athlete and i sweat gallons i dont wear a lot of makeup but i have adult acne blemishes and dark spots that no one ever sees thanks to a combination of products starting with this primer i dont use a lot and i rub it in my skin immediately as once it dries thats it it stays put and so will whatever you apply on top of it so careful a little goes a long way and you must spread it well and thin it feels thick but once rubbed in your fingers it kind of gets more malleable i only put in my t zone and cheeks avoiding eye area completely otherwise it will pull your skin and make you look wrinklyi dab a little mac concealer over the blemishes and spots spray a brush with airbrush foundation jerome alexander or dior and a bit of powder mac fit or inexpensive coty mineral translucent and boom perfect looking face even my dermatologist compliments me on how my face looks and how i cover up my uneven color and blemishesi dont put a picture here of before and after i should but im not going to embarrass myself with my before look it works for some people like me i hope this works for you because for me this was a life changer from sweaty makeup mess and nosy people asking about my blemishes and dark spots rude now no one has to obsess over my post  acne blemishes and we all can move on to truly important thingsfyis no scent a tube lasts me about two months of daily use not sold anymore in my local pharmacy hard to find not sure why i have combination skin that is dry on the forehead acne prone no issues with clogged pores or pimples

title: super matte  not for the faint of heart
review: alright so i just received this and am gonna list my thoughts on a first impression basisit has the look and consistency of very thick petroleum jelly to the point where it takes a bit of muscle to squeeze out of the tube i got a bit skeptical because ive used clear primers in the past the smashbox one and maybelline master prime that havent lived up to their claims of blurring pores and making your makeup last i also was thinking it may be difficult to spread evenly over the skin since its sooo thiccccc but just like with petroleum jelly once it hits the warmth of your skin it just melts into a much more malleable consistencythis is when the stuff starts to behave very differently from your everyday vaselineinstead of sitting on top of your skin in a layer of grease it fully absorbs into your pores and any trace of oil or moisture is gone so are your pores the skin on my face literally feels tightthat being said whoo be carefuli have hyperhidrosis aka excessive sweating especially from my head and face which is like the suckiest thing ever  and the reason i mention it is because i have tried antiperspirant face lotions that feel a lot like this i couldnt find a list of ingredients on the package but if i had to guess i would say that this stuff contains aluminum maybe even a lot of it which will clog your pores and form a barrier between your skin and the oxygen in other words if you are super oily and acneprone like i used to be this will help control it for a special occasion here and there but will make your skin  worse in the long run if you use it on a regular basis  again thats only my first impression but if your skin does not take kindly to strange new cosmetic formulas i would use this stuff very sparinglymy skin does get noticeably more oily in the summer and i usually love a matte primer but this is the first time i felt like a product made my skin look dried out and wrinkled i bought it thinking it would help my makeup wear longer i had no expectations that it would be so matte and blurring im shook if you cant tell loloverall  i really really like this primer and if i had to bet i would say its going to keep my makeup in place  longer than any other ive tried but its also a weapon you must use with caution lol

title: doesnt fully clean but its not the worst

title: a great device but

review: note well  do as much research as possible on the color youre thinking about getting as i had the misfortune of purchasing an everyday shade lead the way that was wayyyy too pale for my complexion as it wasnt returnable i basically gave it to my fairerskinned mom as a gift watch tiktoks and youtube reviews with people close to your coloring to get a real idea of what it will look like on you as the pictures can and even tend to be inaccurate and make sure you know whether its returnable before you buy that coloras for the product itself its really exceptional for such a good price feels great on your lips lasts a crazy long time unlikely to get on your teeth  just a really great lipstick i falling toward a more olive complexion with yellow undertones  found the best to beown your empire is an absolutely perfect red think peggy carter from captain america im in love with it just on the slightest blue side of the orangeblue red lipstick scale anyone whos had issues with their one red lipstick being a little too orange this ones for youpave the road is an excellent subtle shade thats just slightly darker and richer than my natural lip color  really great for everydaychase dreams is a more fun slightly lavendertilted option for when youre wearing clothes that dont look great with straightup redim one of those people who frowns at paying  for one lipstick but its really worth it  good luck

review: they are not that soft i have seen better ones in the drug store but for value they will suffice  i have used a couple of the brushes only thus far  specifically for the  exact reason i purchased them  i am experimenting with cheekbone beauty products but i  find that just using my fingers is not sufficient  so i have used  of the larger brushes to  blend that product out  using a color for undereye concealer  and it works okay but it definitely  is not as soft as i was expecting for that delicate area  none of them are  the smaller brushes  are too small for that purpose  i just fell that although the price point is great they are not the best budget  brushes out therei was never a big fan of makeup when i was younger and did makeup  daily it consisted of  eyeshadow liner mascara a bit of blush  and a lip gloss  now that i am older i rarely  wear any makeup my eyelashes seem to be shorter and i have dark circles under my eyes  so my main  purpose today is if i am going out to look less tired i use some concealer  do my  very sparse eyebrows and  a touch of  mascara maybe a little blush and of course a lip balm  most of the brushes i got in this set for me go unused unless i decide to  do what i once did but  i do not feel the need to  i did go to the drug store and get another brush  that is much softer  and there is a world of difference in how soft it is compared to these  but it is a different brush a size that is not included in this set  i have also used one of the brushes for the  cheekbone beauty primer stick  to  stipple it on as that makes it easier to use the  unify fair as a concealer on that very delicate under eye area  i personally would not recommend purchasing this set  and i will eventually  get the brushes i  want that yes do cost more but are softer and less likely to pull and tug on your skin  once i  play with more eye makeup like shadows i may  see how well the smaller brushes do for that but for now for what i need these were not the best choice

title: i had no idea what i was missing
review: background thought id write this up because as a person who prefers sheer but effective foundation  concealer coverage and spends a lot of time in front of cameras for my job as an online instructor to a global audience in hd finding stuff that makes my skin feel fresh  flawless at  is important to me not only for the cameras but for myself tooi bought this concealer brush as a bit of an impulse buy during prime day along with a new foundation brush because id seen various makeup videos on youtube using similar ones i have always used my fingers and had no idea that a brush would give such superior resultsi have very naturally youthful wrinklefree skin for my age but my skin is getting more delicate and thinner my night owl tendencies are more obvious under my eyes as wellbeing able to more precisely  delicately apply  manipulate concealer is a godsendand when concealer is settling into the under eye skin you can easily use this brush after wiping off any excess product on the bristles to sweep away any concealer that has collected in the fine crease under the lash lineive tried it with three different liquid concealers of various price points nyx hd too faced and make up for ever hd all went on beautifully and id rate them in that order too make up for ever being the most impressive finishi am hookedi only recently switched to using a foundation brush a cheap one but it has converted me so i cant wait until the real techniques one i also bought on prime day arriveswhen cash allows ill upgrade from both of these by real techniques to prolevel brushes but for now for now i look better than ever before and am thrilled

title: i might have messed mine up
review: this is my first time using a product like this i have never washed my brushes thats a liei washed a couple of them about  years ago with just soap and water and they stayed damp forever and i then i couldnt use them for days but ive been seeing these kits on buzzfeed for years now and since im approaching  im trying to take better care of myself i didnt look at the instructions before my first attempt it comes with these  little white pegs i put it on incorrectly the first time and i had to use a kitchen tool to remove it with quite a bit of force then i see the instructions and it says that once its in there dont remove it so i have no idea why they sent  of its not meant to be replaced anyway i got the hang of it but i dont know if i messed something up with the yanking or if its just the weight of the brushes when i turn it on i have to start the spinning off with my hand again that might be my fault it is very cool to watch though i like how quickly they dry with the spinning if they made stuff like this when i was in my youth then yes i wouldve washed my brushes regularly like i seriously have one powder brush that ive had for over  years and this was the first time it was cleaned be careful with the big brushes though and how you store them after cleaning the wand on that one broke off years ago but its so big that i didnt need it i have a mug that i set all of my brushes in and bc i dont have the stem on that brush it went into the mug and got beaten up by other brush stems when i finally went to use that one again the fibers were going every which way i dont know if i ruined the brush ill try to wash it again and hopefully the shape comes backbut if it doesnt well ive been needed to retire that thing for years now

title: great product however it has some downsides
review: i bought this because i need to clean my brushes regularly or i get really bad breakouts and stys but that takes a lot of time and sometimes with denser brushes soapy residue is really hard to get out which annoys me to no end let me start by saying it works it doesnt get all the staining out if you use bright colors like i like to do but it gets all the pigment out if you have double sided brushes this could be a problem if you want to clean both sides because chances are that you will only be able to clean the larger side of the brush because the attachment wont fit if you turn it around to clean the other side itll just screw up your brush and fly off but it came with enough attachments to fit all of my brushes another thing make sure you have multiple triple a batteries in rotation before you start using this this thing eats through them like no ones business so buy the value pack if you have a lot of brushes like i do but its a small price to pay for your sanity as id rather buy more batteries then go back to scrubbing my brushes constantly all and all its a good product and would recommend buying it if youre like me and have to wash a lot of brushes constantly

title: works but not like magic
review: its been a long time since ive cleaned my brushes lets just say that my foundation brush is newer but it was still pretty filthy as the bristles are very compact it took a few sessions to really get that my powder  blushhighlighter brushes very clean what i suggest you do is fill an empty water bottle with lukewarm water  soapbrush cleaner youll use that to refill your cleansing bowl have a secondary container to place the used water infollow the directions provided in the packaging but without drying your brushes completely check your bristles to see if you need to continue cleaning i typically only had to do this on the large face brushes if the water is starting to get very dirty i discard it in the second bowl  refill the the water bottle once clean dry all the waythe smaller brushes dry very quickly for the most part so be careful not to over dry them i suggest drying them slowly  reshaping the bristles as you go its very easy to overspin  ended up with your bristles bushy

title: great mirror ive had for  years now fyi the photo shows the extension but it comes separately
review: nice mirror and i love it ive come back almost two years after buying the mirror to write a review because i realize that of all the things ive bought on amazon over the years this mirror is not only the thing i use daily but its been the most practical and reliable thing i own it deserves a great review i use it mostly at home but there have been days in which ive had to rush out of the house without my makeup so i grab my makeup bag and the mirror and ill put my makeup on in a parking lot later that day just place the suction cup from the extension onto your windshield and voila youre good to go sometimes the suction needs a little moisture i mean thats something i thought everyone knew but apparently some people are writing in their reviews that the suction doesnt work  im pretty sure theyre not putting a little moisture from the faucet if youre in the bathroom but a little lick will do in a pinch dont say gross youve all done it  on the suction cup will make it work just fine unless the suction cup happens to be defective which i doubtthe mirror works great it does need batteries so i bought the amazon rechargeable batteries and charger specifically for this mirror because it might end up using  aa batteries about once a month depending on how long it takes to do your makeup my kids also use the mirror for some reason despite the fact that they have perfect vision so our batteries wear out fairly quickly as well as the fact that i use the mirror daily and for at least  an hour a day amazon rechargeable batteries dont keep the brightness as long but as long as you dont mind charging them regularly thats fine otherwise regular batteries keep the brightness for a lot longer  its sturdy too ive dropped it many times due to clumsiness and it keeps on tickinglastly as i recall the company is woman owned so thats another plus if youre about to turn  or you know a contact lense wearer or makeup wearer or even a skin care enthusiast get it for yourself or a friend its definitely worth it i should add that i just remembered that when i originally ordered the mirror it didnt come with the extension and it was during covid so not only did i have to wait for it for almost a month but had to pay extra for something i assumed came with it since the photo included the extension so theres that but it was worth it honestly i think they should just include the extension and charge more because i dont see how anyone could use it without it it doesnt really stand up on its own i dont believe

title: great zoeva dupes natural hair brushes have a learning curve
review: white hair brushes typically indicate animal natural hair these are meant for dense application of powder products the black hair brushes are synthetic for cream and liquid products they dont soak up the product as much as natural hair does and lighter powder application they dont grab powder as well as natural hair thats why the eyeshadow brushes and blush highlight etc brushes in this set are natural hair and the foundation duo fiber brow and powder are synthetic you want a light dusting of powder for all over its hard to find natural hair brushes in this price range and these are really good they are a naturalsynthetic blend thats also why some people are saying the white hair brushes shed and fray more than the synthetic black ones thats not uncommon and they may not be washing them properly please research how to wash your natural hair brushes condition them or use oil to keep them from fraying treat them like your own hair natural hair brushes will change your makeup game these brushes are meant to be zoeva dupes down to the name and number on the handle and the naturalsynthetic composition i own some of the z ones these are meant to dupe and jessup are really good quality for the price the z ones are a little softer but even those can shed a bit at first ive included a comparison photo i havent washed the jessup brushes yet so ill update once i do about how they hold their shape most of the brushes are pretty self explanatory but some of them might seem superfluous some suggestions for the ones that seem extra  face shape for cream contour  petit stippling for targeted bronzer  luxe face definer for diffused bronzer  luxe face paint for powder contour and  stippling for light liquid foundation or tinted moisturizeroverall this is a lovely comprehensive brush set ive had them about a month the eye brushes are especially impressive you can do any look with this range the synthetic face brushes rival zoeva quality except the z ones are heavier without sparkles on handle but who cares the white hair brushes are also very good all brushes are dense so soft great blending dont leave streaks solid construction these jessup brushes are a steal you can find cheaper brush sets on amazon but they will be synthetic bristles these are some very good quality brushes  recommend

title: the only review you need to read get it
review: if youre a cheapo that likes high quality things such as myself these brushes are perfect they are very comparable to morphe brushes and dare i say these jessup brushes are even better theyre soft without feeling plasticy only one really had a synthetic feel to it which is the  stippling brush and they apply makeup better than a lot of higherend brushes that ive tried in the past i got the color in blushing bride and they are absolutely beautiful all of the brushes come individually packaged in a plastic wrapper the bigger fluffier brushes have a netlike thing on the bristles which protects them only  brushes are shown in the picture because one brush had rolled under my leg so none were missing ive seen reviews complaining about a hair or two being out of place but personally i see no issue in that none of my brushes were shedding or fuzzylookingim not a picky person but if your brushes dont come in in tiptop shape send them back and get a new batch because these are worth it despite any minor flawi only used  of the  brushes to apply my makeup for the look i created in these pictures for my everyday routine i used all of my same products however i did not apply or blend my foundation with any of the brushes out of preference so i cant say how these brushes would handle blending liquid foundationbrushes usedi used the  luxe highlight brush to apply my settingbaking powder as shown in the second picture and it picked up my fenty beauty setting powder really well and applied just how i wanted it to face shape brush essence powder contour around face and nose this brush is super small to be contouring or bronzing the cheeks but none of the others seemed to be the right shape or density besides the brush i had already used to apply my blush luxe sheer cheek brush nars powder blush this one didnt apply my blush exactly how i liked so i would simply use a different brush next time this one wouldve been the better cheek contour brush for its shape brow liner brows using abh dip brow pomade was a bit big for applying this product so next time i would swap it out for the  detail liner brush disclaimer none of these eye brushes have a spoolie to brush and blend out brow products luxe crease  luxe soft definer and  smudger brushes eyeshadow with my glamlite chocolate donut palette and the chocolates palette by juvias place these eyeshadow brushes really knocked everything out of the park even though i only used  of the  eye brushes in this pc setkeep in mind to not rely solely on pictures of how makeup applied for others in reviews because makeup primer brand and skills or lack of those things can affect how these brushes will appear to performall of the brushes are different so dont expect multiples if you do lots of colorful eyeshadow looks very often i would purchase this set along with jessups brush set that comes with just the  or  eye brushes which is  if im remembering correctlyi cannot say for certain how these brushes would hold up during a wash because i try not to wash my makeup brushes as often as i should but these are so nice that i wouldnt even mind if they got a little bit beat up because i would keep using them and continue buying more these would be an amazing gift to anyone that has a love for makeup or even anyone that is a beginner in the makeup world
